* Start the VM
  - with default CPU (pae)

        kvm -cdrom tails.iso -m 5120 -no-reboot -no-shutdown

  - with 486 CPU

        kvm -cpu 486 -cdrom tails.iso -m 5120 -no-reboot -no-shutdown -snapshot

* Open the qemu console (CTRL-ALT-2).
* Save physical memory to the `tails.dump` file (length is an integer, max size for one dump is 4G):

        pmemsave <start adsress> <length> <filename>

        pmemsave 0 0xF0000000 tails14.dump
        pmemsave 0x100000000 0x40000000 tails5.dump
